<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="0c15a5b2-4577-4783-a2fb-a856238de6b1" >

    <h2>Students Conducting Research</h2> 
<p>Any students wanting to conduct research must have a faculty supervisor. Graduate students must apply for ethics review through the same process as faculty researchers through the Online Ethics Protocol Submission and Review System, which can be accessed through your <a href="http://my.ryerson.ca/" target="_blank">my.ryerson<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, opens in new window</span></a> account. Prior to submitting the online application for ethics approval, graduate students are required to register and complete the&nbsp;<a href="https://tcps2core.ca/welcome" target="_blank">TCPS online tutorial<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link, opens in new window</span></a>.</p> 
<h3>Students as Participants in Research</h3> 
<p>The following provides information for research involving student participants:<br> </p> 
<ul> 
 <li><a target="_blank" href="/content/dam/research/documents/ethics/REB%20Student%20Bill%20of%20Rights%20and%20Responsibilities%20Students%20as%20Research%20Participants.docx"><span class="sr-only">word file</span>Guidelines for Student Research Participant Pools<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-file-word-o"></span><span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, opens in new window</span></a></li> 
</ul>
    





